    "**Problem: Variable-Length Sequences**\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "[3, 1, 2, 5]\n",
    "[4, 1, 2, 6]\n",
    "[3, 1]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "# Padding\n",
    "\n",
    "## Padding: Why Do We Need It?\n",
    "\n",
    "### Problem: Variable-Length Sequences\n",
    "\n",
    "Text sequences have different lengths:\n",
    "\n",
    "`[3, 1, 2, 5]`\n",
    "\n",
    "`[4, 1]`\n",
    "\n",
    "Neural networks require:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "(\\text{batch}, \\text{fixed length})\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "> Cannot stack sequences directly into tensors\n",
    "\n",
    "### Solution: Padding\n",
    "\n",
    "Add special token (0) to standardize length:\n",
    "\n",
    "[4, 1] → [4, 1, 0, 0]\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.callout-tip title=\"Key Idea\"}\n",
    "Padding = making data rectangular\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Padding Sequences"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "306d8541",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[[4 2 3 5]\n",
      " [6 2 3 7]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.sequence import pad_sequences\n",
    "\n",
    "padded = pad_sequences(sequences, padding='post')\n",
    "print(padded)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1cd0b7bc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Padding: Subtleties & Consequences\n",
    "\n",
    "**Types of Padding**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Post-padding (preferred in NLP)\n",
    "    - `[real data | padding]`\n",
    "- Pre-padding\n",
    "    - `[padding | real data]`\n",
    "\n",
    "**Hidden Problem**\n",
    "\n",
    "Padding introduces fake data (zeros)\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.callout-warning}\n",
    "Model may learn: *“zero is important”*.\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "**Implication**\n",
    "\n",
    "Padding must be handled carefully\n",
    "\n",
    "- Leads to masking\n",
    "\n",
    "# Embeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "## Embeddings\n",
    "\n",
    "- Dense vector representation of tokens\n",
    "- Captures semantic meaning\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Embeddings: From Tokens to Vectors\n",
    "\n",
    "### Core Idea\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "w \\rightarrow \\mathbf{e}_w \\in \\mathbb{R}^d\n",
    "$$​\n",
    "\n",
    "### Embedding Matrix\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\mathbf{E} \\in \\mathbb{R}^{V \\times d}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "- $V$: vocabulary size\n",
    "- $d$: embedding dimension\n",
    "\n",
    "**Lookup**\n",
    "\n",
    "- Input:  `[3, 1, 2]`\n",
    "- Output: `[E[3], E[1], E[2]]`\n",
    "\n",
    "> Trainable lookup table\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why Embeddings Work\n",
    "\n",
    "### Semantic Geometry\n",
    "\n",
    "Similar words → close vectors\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.callout title=\"Example\"}\n",
    "king - man + woman ≈ queen\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "### vs One-Hot Encoding\n",
    "\n",
    "| One-hot    | Embedding        |\n",
    "| ---------- | ---------------- |\n",
    "| Sparse     | Dense            |\n",
    "| No meaning | Semantic meaning |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Training\n",
    "\n",
    "- Learned via backpropagation\n",
    "- Only used columns are updated\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Embedding Layer"
   ]
  },
