    "# Masking\n",
    "\n",
    "## Masking: Ignoring Fake Data\n",
    "\n",
    "### Problem\n",
    "\n",
    "Padding introduces noise:\n",
    "\n",
    "`[3, 1, 0, 0]`\n",
    "\n",
    ">Model should ignore zeros\n",
    "\n",
    "### Solution: Masking\n",
    "\n",
    "Mask tensor:\n",
    "\n",
    "`[1, 1, 0, 0]`\n",
    "\n",
    "- 1 → real data\n",
    "- 0 → ignore\n",
    "\n",
    "**TensorFlow Example**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "fbb222a4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "embedding = tf.keras.layers.Embedding(\n",
    "    input_dim=10000,\n",
    "    output_dim=64,\n",
    "    mask_zero=True\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7a7a4042",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Masking: Special Cases\n",
    "\n",
    "Where It Works:\n",
    "\n",
    "- LSTM / GRU\n",
    "- RNNs\n",
    "- Attention layers\n",
    "\n",
    ":::{.callout-important title=\"Time Series\"}\n",
    "In time series, masking is not limited to zero values.\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing data may be encoded as:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `NaN`\n",
    "- `-1`\n",
    "- sentinel values (e.g., `-999`)\n",
    "- domain-specific flags\n",
    ":::\n",
    "\n",
    "Mask must be explicitly defined, e.g.:"
   ]
